race.comment: FEE TRAIN (5) was prominent on the corner and battled on well to finish second last start over 201m at this track (Dirt), beaten a nose when fresh from a spell as favourite. Has his share of talent. Hard to beat in this suitable race. EL MONDAYS CAPO (1) missed the placings two starts back then ran a better race and finished 1.75 lengths away in fifth last time out over 402m at The Albuquerque Downs Racetrack & Casino. Meeting a deeper field this time but he has the ability to mix it with them. DIVERS DO IT D PER (3) missed the placings two runs back then improved last start but found one better over 229m at Prairie Meadows, beaten only 0.1 lengths after being prominent at the corner. Well placed and there is no reason he cannot find winning ways. ONE BAD FDD (6) is a five-start maiden who looks close to breaking the duck after finishing in the placings at his last couple of runs, most recently when one length away in second over 320m at this track. Sure to be in the mix again.
